This is a COMPLETE Web3 DeFi app with working swap interface supporting both 0G Mainnet and Testnet.

NETWORKS SUPPORTED:
- **Mainnet (16661)**: Real swaps via Janie DEX (Uniswap V3 style) - DEFAULT
- **Testnet (16602)**: Demo mode for development (no DEX deployed)

WHAT'S ALREADY BUILT:
- Tab navigation: Swap, Pools, Chart, Portfolio
- Working swap UI with real V3 execution on mainnet
- Token selection with balance display and MAX button
- Slippage and deadline settings
- Transaction status modal with explorer links
- Wallet connection via RainbowKit
- Premium glassmorphism design with animated background
- Config-driven feature toggles

DEX CONTRACTS (Mainnet - Janie DEX):
- Router: 0x8b598a7c136215a95ba0282b4d832b9f9801f2e2
- Factory: 0x9bdca5798e52e592a08e3b34d3f18eef76af7ef4
- W0G: 0x1cd0690ff9a693f5ef2dd976660a8dafc81a109c
- USDC.e: 0x1f3aa82227281ca364bfb3d253b0f1af1da6473e

PRE-BUILT COMPONENTS:

UI Components (src/components/ui/):
- GlassCard, GlassButton, GlassInput - Glassmorphism design system
- Shimmer - Loading skeleton
- AnimatedBackground - Gradient mesh background
- GradientText, NumberFlow - Text effects

Web3 Components (src/components/web3/):
- Primitives: TokenIcon, TokenBalance, TokenInput, TokenInputField, ConnectButton, NetworkBadge, ExplorerLink, TxStatusModal, SwapSettings, SwapSettingsPanel, TokenSelectModal
- Feature Panels (-panel suffix): SwapPanel, PoolsPanel, ChartPanel, PortfolioPanel
- Layout: Header

NAMING CONVENTIONS:
- Feature panels use `-panel` suffix: swap-panel.tsx, pools-panel.tsx
- All files in kebab-case
- To add new features: create web3/[feature]-panel.tsx

FEATURE CONFIG (src/config/features.ts):
- Toggle features via FeatureProvider in main.tsx
- Available toggles: swap, pools, chart, portfolio
- Sub-toggles: showChart, showPriceImpact, showNetworkFee, animatedBackground, etc.

COMMON CUSTOMIZATIONS:
- "Change colors" → Edit tailwind.config.js theme.extend.colors
- "Add token balances" → Use <TokenBalanceList /> component
- "Add new panel" → Create web3/[name]-panel.tsx, add to features.ts
- "Add new token" → Edit src/constants/tokens.ts MAINNET_TOKENS or TESTNET_TOKENS
- "Change default network" → Edit src/config/chains.ts defaultChain
- "Disable a feature" → Set enabled: false in FeatureProvider config
- "Swap only mode" → Use MINIMAL_FEATURES preset from features.ts

NETWORK INFO:
- Mainnet Explorer: https://chainscan.0g.ai
- Testnet Explorer: https://chainscan-galileo.0g.ai
- Bridge: https://hub.0g.ai/bridge
- Testnet Faucet: https://faucet.0g.ai

FILE STRUCTURE:
- src/config/chains.ts → Chain definitions (mainnet + testnet)
- src/config/features.ts → Feature configuration system
- src/config/wagmi.ts → Wallet configuration
- src/constants/contracts.ts → DEX contract addresses by network
- src/constants/tokens.ts → Token lists by network
- src/constants/pools.ts → Pool configurations by network
- src/constants/abis.ts → Contract ABIs (V3 Router, ERC20, Pool)
- src/hooks/useSwap.ts → Swap execution logic
- src/hooks/usePools.ts → Pool data fetching
- src/hooks/usePortfolio.ts → Portfolio balance tracking
- src/providers/feature-provider.tsx → Feature config context
- src/components/ui/ → Glassmorphism design components
- src/components/web3/ → All Web3 components (primitives + panels)

DATA MODES:
- Mainnet: Real swap execution, real token balances, demo chart/pools data
- Testnet: Demo mode for all features (no DEX deployed)
- "Demo Data" badges shown when using mock data

For stock photos, use images from Unsplash with valid URLs.
